I put on a dress shirt and a tie for this fucking meeting, and sweater-britches comes to complain about some shit on her desk being moved. 

Telling someone to "knock it off" in a professional manner is not a skill I possess yet.

As a kid, "interrupting a meeting" seemed like not that big a deal because meetings are often a waste of time. But as a barely adult, even I can figure out that if I have a gripe with someone, it waits until the outside vendors are out of their office.

In a meeting with an outside vendor and our insurance broker, we were interrupted by one of the office staff who had a hissy fit about something on her desk being moved, and let me tell you: I haven't been this mad at someone who works at the same place I do in quite some time.
